# Elder-Fraud Exploitation State Machine Extension (T-Box + phase/action vocabulary)
#
# Narrow, machine-only extension: contributes ONLY what the trajectories
# (traj:) Exploitation State Machine needs to run on a grandparent-scam /
# transnational elder-fraud offense — a skos:ConceptScheme of traj:State
# phases and a small catalog of uco-action:Technique-typed action classes.
# It is deliberately NOT a rich domain ontology: no class hierarchy beyond
# the Technique metaclass punning pattern already established by
# extensions/attack-technique, and no elder-fraud-specific taxonomy of
# victims, instruments, or roles (those stay as ordinary UCO/uco-identity
# nodes in the exemplar).
#
# Phase set grounded in United States v. Oscar Manuel Castanos Garcia, et
# al., No. 1:24-cr-10138-LTS (D. Mass.). Both sources are public DOJ URLs
# (no PACER, nothing vendored in-repo):
#   PR  -- USAO-MA press release "Operators of Transnational Elder Fraud
#          Scheme Plead Guilty" (2026-07-15):
#          https://www.justice.gov/usao-ma/pr/operators-transnational-elder-fraud-scheme-plead-guilty
#   Aff -- Detention Affidavit, USA v. Oscar Manuel Castanos Garcia, et al.,
#          publicly hosted at:
#          https://www.justice.gov/usao-ma/media/1410886/dl?inline
#          (Affiant identity and internal paragraph numbering are not
#          asserted here — not traceable without fetching the PDF, which
#          this extension does not vendor. Citations below are document-
#          level: "Aff." vs "PR", not pinpoint.)
#
# Offense phases (S):
#   InitialContact         -- "Opener" cold-calls victim impersonating a
#                              grandchild in trouble (Aff.).
#   Conditioning            -- "Closer" impersonates the grandchild's
#                              attorney and demands bail/fee money (Aff.).
#   ExtractionInstruction   -- Closer (posing as the grandchild's attorney)
#                              directs the payment mechanism: cash form and
#                              hand-off via rideshare/"documents" pickup,
#                              commercial-carrier shipment, or delivery
#                              (Aff.; produced by a_direct).
#   ProceedsCollection      -- A US-based runner (via unwitting rideshare
#                              driver or carrier delivery) physically
#                              obtains the cash (Aff.).
#   Laundering              -- Proceeds are deposited into bank accounts in
#                              the names of purported businesses, structured
#                              below the $10,000 CTR threshold (Aff.).
# Terminal outcome states (F), reached by transition (not mid-offense phases):
#   Completed               -- Cross-border transmission of laundered proceeds
#                              realized the modeled endpoint (Aff.).
#   (Disrupted is carried as traj:terminalPolarity on a mid-chain terminal
#    PhaseAssertion — e.g. Attleboro arrest at ProceedsCollection — rather
#    than as a separate traj:State, matching the trajectories metamodel.)
#
# Authoritative transition function T (arriving-state enactsAction; multi-
# action edges are multi-valued). FACT CORRECTION vs an earlier ESM draft:
# Aff. places the secrecy line ("keep this between us until i get out") in
# the OPENER script (InitialContact), not the Closer/Conditioning phase —
# so a_secrecy gates InitialContact -> Conditioning with a_spoof/a_script.
# a_direct (payment-mechanism direction by the Closer) produces
# ExtractionInstruction.
#
#   InitialContact --a_spoof, a_script, a_secrecy--> Conditioning
#   Conditioning --a_direct--> ExtractionInstruction
#   ExtractionInstruction --a_coopt--> ProceedsCollection
#   ProceedsCollection --a_fakeid, a_deposit--> Laundering
#   Laundering --a_transmit--> Completed
#
# Terminal polarity: Agawam full run ends Completed/"completed"; Attleboro
# UPS pickup is mid-chain interrupted at ProceedsCollection/"disrupted"
# (Tavarez Jimenez arrested collecting the second package) (Aff.).
#
# Exogenous pre-s0: victim-list purchase is a prov:Activity feeding
# InitialContact — NOT a member of S (Aff.: operators purchased elderly-
# victim lists).

@prefix ef: <http://example.org/ontology/elder-fraud/> .
@prefix traj: <http://example.org/ontology/trajectories/> .
@prefix uco-core: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/core/> .
@prefix uco-action: <https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/action/> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix dcterms: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

<http://example.org/ontology/elder-fraud>
	a owl:Ontology ;
	rdfs:label "Elder-Fraud Exploitation State Machine Extension"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Phase vocabulary (traj:State plug-in) and Technique-typed action catalog for a transnational grandparent-scam / elder-fraud Exploitation State Machine. Grounded in United States v. Castanos Garcia et al., No. 1:24-cr-10138-LTS (D. Mass.). Depends on the trajectories and attack-technique extensions; mints no domain taxonomy beyond phases and actions."@en ;
	dcterms:source
		"https://www.justice.gov/usao-ma/pr/operators-transnational-elder-fraud-scheme-plead-guilty"^^xsd:anyURI ,
		"https://www.justice.gov/usao-ma/media/1410886/dl?inline"^^xsd:anyURI ;
	owl:imports
		<http://example.org/ontology/trajectories> ,
		<https://ontology.unifiedcyberontology.org/uco/action/> .

#################################################################
# Phase vocabulary: traj:State instances in a SKOS scheme
#################################################################

ef:PhaseScheme
	a skos:ConceptScheme ;
	skos:prefLabel "Elder-fraud (grandparent-scam) offense phases"@en ;
	dcterms:source "United States v. Castanos Garcia et al., No. 1:24-cr-10138-LTS (D. Mass.), Detention Affidavit, publicly hosted at https://www.justice.gov/usao-ma/media/1410886/dl?inline"@en .

ef:InitialContact
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Initial contact" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Initial contact"@en ;
	skos:definition "'Opener' call-center employee cold-calls the elderly victim, impersonating a grandchild who was in an accident; VoIP spoofing makes the call appear to originate from a U.S. number; the opener script includes an isolation instruction ('keep this between us until i get out'). Source: Aff. (opener script photos)."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

ef:Conditioning
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Conditioning" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Conditioning"@en ;
	skos:definition "'Closer' call-center employee follows up, impersonating the grandchild's attorney, and directs the victim to send or deliver cash to aid the grandchild (bail/fee demand). Source: Aff. (closers impersonated attorneys and directed cash payment)."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

ef:ExtractionInstruction
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Extraction instruction" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Extraction instruction"@en ;
	skos:definition "The Closer (posing as the grandchild's attorney) directs the victim into a concrete payment mechanism — cash form and hand-off via rideshare pickup framed as 'documents,' commercial-carrier shipment, or delivery — converting conditioned compliance into logistics. Source: Aff. (closers directed victims to send or deliver cash; rideshare/'documents' and UPS shipment mechanisms)."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

ef:ProceedsCollection
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Proceeds collection" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Proceeds collection"@en ;
	skos:definition "A U.S.-based runner obtains the cash, typically via an unwitting rideshare driver or carrier delivery, and moves it toward the operation's deposit/hand-off channel. Source: Aff."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

ef:Laundering
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Laundering" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Laundering"@en ;
	skos:definition "Proceeds are deposited into bank accounts held in the names of purported businesses and structured in amounts below the $10,000 currency-transaction-report threshold. Source: Aff."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

ef:Completed
	a traj:State , skos:Concept ;
	uco-core:name "Completed" ;
	skos:prefLabel "Completed"@en ;
	skos:definition "Terminal outcome state: laundered scam proceeds have been transmitted or hand-delivered from the United States to the Dominican Republic, realizing the modeled offense endpoint. Source: Aff. (fee-based cross-border transmission)."@en ;
	skos:inScheme ef:PhaseScheme .

#################################################################
# Action catalog: Technique-typed uco-action:Action subclasses
# (metaclass punning pattern per extensions/attack-technique)
#################################################################

ef:a_spoof
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Caller-ID / VoIP spoofing"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Use of Voice over IP technology to place calls over the internet so that they appear to originate from a U.S. telephone number, concealing the call center's true (Dominican Republic) origin. Source: Aff."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T1" .

ef:a_script
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Fixed-script deployment"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Deployment of pre-authored call-center scripts that openers (and related roles) follow when cold-calling victims — e.g. the photographed opener script recovered from a CASTANOS GARCIA call center. Source: Aff. (call-center managers provided employees with scripts; opener-script photos)."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T2" .

ef:a_secrecy
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Isolation / secrecy instruction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Instructing the victim to isolate the matter from others — in the Aff. opener script, the grandchild persona asks the victim to 'keep this between us until i get out.' Source: Aff. (opener script). FACT NOTE: this language is in the OPENER (InitialContact) script, not the Closer/Conditioning phase."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T3" .

ef:a_direct
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Payment-mechanism direction"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "The Closer (posing as the grandchild's attorney) specifies the cash form and hand-off method — courier/rideshare pickup, commercial-carrier shipment, or delivery — that converts the conditioned victim into executing a concrete payment. Operational pivot from emotional conditioning to logistics; produces ExtractionInstruction. Source: Aff. (closers 'directed the victims to send or deliver cash'; rideshare packages framed as 'documents'; UPS cash shipment to runner addresses)."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T8" .

ef:a_coopt
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Co-opting an unwitting intermediary"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Directing an unwitting third party — most often a rideshare driver, occasionally a relative sent by a co-conspirator — to physically collect or relay a cash package from the victim without the intermediary's knowledge that a fraud is underway. Source: Aff. (rideshare driver messaged to collect 'documents' from a 'grandmother')."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T4" .

ef:a_fakeid
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Fabricated identity / purported-business account"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Routing scam proceeds through bank accounts held in the names of purported (non-existent) businesses — e.g. a Bank of America account in the name of a purported vape-supply wholesaler supplied by NUÑEZ NUÑEZ. Source: Aff. (STRUCTURAL wiring: ProceedsCollection -> Laundering. Closers also impersonate attorneys per Aff., but that fact is carried in Conditioning occupancy text, not as this Technique's arriving-edge action.)"@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T5" .

ef:a_deposit
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Deposit structuring"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Deposit structuring <$10k to evade BSA reporting: depositing scam-proceeds cash in amounts kept below the $10,000 currency-transaction-report threshold to avoid Bank Secrecy Act reporting obligations. Source: Aff. (deposits typically structured between $7,000 and $9,500)."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T6" .

ef:a_transmit
	a owl:Class , uco-action:Technique ;
	rdfs:subClassOf uco-action:Action ;
	rdfs:label "Cross-border proceeds transmission"@en ;
	rdfs:comment "Transmitting or hand-delivering collected scam proceeds from the United States to the Dominican Republic through a money-transmitter/courier network, for a fee — the action that produces the Completed terminal. Source: Aff. (money transmitter charged an eight percent fee; runner-to-nephew hand deliveries in New York)."@en ;
	uco-action:techniqueID "EF.T7" .
